# Model-first reasoning (anti-rules)

This project aims at a JARVIS-like local assistant. Architecture: `docs/JARVIS_ARCHITECTURE.md`.

## Law

**The model reasons. Code provides tools and safety. Do not grow keyword/regex dictionaries to "understand" language.**

## Never do

- Add `if "who is"` / `if "who are"` / synonym lists to fix intent
- Expand long marker tuples whenever a new phrasing fails
- Replace thinking/tool-calling with another heuristic branch "just this once"

## Do instead

1. Improve **LLM planner/router prompts** (principles, not checklists)
2. Enable/keep **model thinking** where appropriate (desktop profile)
3. Add a **typed tool** (launch app, search, screen) with JSON schema + whitelist
4. Pass richer **Sense context** (active window, inventory) into the model

## Allowed in code

- OS/hardware plumbing (capture, windows, hotkeys, single-instance)
- Safety policy (whitelist, confirm gates)
- Short system principles (interpret user intent naturally)
- Game/content databases (facts), not language routing tables

## Review question before merging NLP-ish logic

> Is this a **tool/capability**, or an attempt to **parse English/Russian with ifs**?

If the latter — reject and use the model.
